ia, LLC|work=tokyohive}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://natalie.mu/music/news/190781|script-title=ja:\u6b05\u574246\u30012nd\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u306f\u300c\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u306f\u611b\u3057\u304b\u306a\u3044\u300d|accessdate=2016-08-10|publisher=Natasha,Inc|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nThe center position in the choreography for the title song is held by [[Yurina Hirate]].<ref name=\"mdpr20160724\">{{cite web|url=http://mdpr.jp/music/detail/1600440|script-title=ja:\u6b05\u574246\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u5e73\u624b\u53cb\u68a8\u5948\u306e\u8868\u73fe\u529b\u306b\u91d8\u4ed8\u3051 \u6c7a\u610f\u304c\u6ef2\u3080\u92ed\u3044\u773c\u5149|accessdate=2016-08-10|publisher=modelpress|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nThe single was number-one on the [[Oricon]] Weekly [[Oricon Singles Chart|Singles Chart]], with 323,066 copies sold.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2016/08/oricon-weekly-charts-for-8-8-8-14|title=Oricon Weekly Charts for 8/8 ~ 8/14|accessdate=2016-09-06|publisher=6Theory Media, LLC|work=tokyohive}}</ref> It was also [[List of Hot 100 number-one singles of 2016 (Japan)|number-one]] on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Japan Hot 100]].<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web|url= http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=hot100&year=2016&month=08&day=22|title= Billboard Japan Hot 100 2016/8/22|work= Billboard Japan|language= Japanese|accessdate=2016-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nIt was released in 4 editions, Type-A, Type-B, Type-C and a regular edition. All editions, except the regular edition, include a DVD with music videos. Type-A includes [[Yurina Hirate]]'s solo song ''Shibuya Kara Parco ga Kieta Hi''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2075616/full/|script-title=ja:\u6b05\u574246\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u5e73\u624b\u53cb\u68a8\u5948\u3001\u9589\u9928\u9593\u8fd1\u306e\u6e0b\u8c37PARCO\u3092\u6b4c\u3046|date=2016-07-24|accessdate=2016-09-14|publisher=oricon ME inc.|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\nThe choreography for the title track was created by Takahiro Ueno. The music video for it was directed by {{illm|Kazuma Ikeda (director)|lt=Kazuma Ikeda|ja|\u6c60\u7530\u4e00\u771f (\u6620\u50cf\u30c7\u30a3\u30ec\u30af\u30bf\u30fc)}} and shot in [[Hokkaid\u014d]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2074955/full/|script-title=ja:\u6b05\u574246\u3001\u65b0\u66f2MV\u306f\u5317\u6d77\u9053\u306e\u8349\u539f\u3067\u30c0\u30f3\u30b9 \u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u5e73\u624b\u304c\u53eb\u3076!|accessdate=2016-08-10|publisher=oricon ME inc.|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n== Track listings ==\nAll lyrics written by [[Yasushi Akimoto]].\n\n=== Type-A ===\n{{tracklist\n| collapsed = \n| headline = CD{{Sfn|Keyakizaka46|2016a}}\n| extra_column = \n| total_length = \n| all_lyrics = \n| writing_credits = \n| lyrics_credits = \n| music_credits = \n| title1 = Sekai ni wa Ai Shika Nai\n| note1 = {{nihongo2|\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u306f\u611b\u3057\u304b\u306a\u3044}}\n| music1 = \n| extra1 = \n| length1 = 4:56\n| title2 = Kataru Nara Mirai o...\n| note2 = {{nihongo2|\u8a9e\u308b\u306a\u3089\u672a\u6765\u3092\u2026}}\n| music2 = \n| extra2 = \n| length2 = 3:52\n| title3 = Shibuya Kara Parco ga Kieta Hi\n| note3 = {{nihongo2|\u6e0b\u8c37\u304b\u3089PARCO\u304c\u6d88\u3048\u305f\u65e5}}\n| music3 = \n| extra3 = \n| length3 = 4:55\n| title4 = Sekai ni wa Ai Shika Nai ([[backing track|off vocal ver.]])\n| length4 = 4:56\n| title5 = Kataru Nara Mirai o... (off vocal ver.)\n| length5 = 3:52\n| title6 = Shibuya Kara Parco ga Kieta Hi (off vocal ver.)\n| length6 = 4:54\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| collapsed = yes\n| headline = DVD{{Sfn|Keyakizaka46|2016a}}\n| extra_column = \n| total_length = \n| title1 = Sekai ni wa Ai Shika Nai Music Video\n| extra1 = \n| length1 = 5:06\n| title2 = Shibuya Kara Parco ga Kieta Hi Music Video\n| extra2 = \n| length2 = 5:18\n| title3 = Nijika Ishimori\n| extra3 = \n| length3 = 4:12\n| title4 = Rika Ozeki\n| extra4 = \n| length4 = 5:38\n| title5 = Manaka Shida\n| ex