{"title_page": "1994 CAA Men's Basketball Tournament", "text_new": "{{Infobox NCAA Basketball Conference Tournament\n| Year           = 1994\n| Conference     = CAA\n| Division       = I\n| Gender         = Men's\n| Image          =\n| ImageSize      = \n| Caption        =  \n| Teams          = 8\n| Arena          = [[Richmond Coliseum]]\n| City           = [[Richmond, Virginia]]\n| Champions      = James Madison\n| TitleCount     = 3rd\n| Coach          = [[Lefty Driesell]]\n| CoachCount     = 1st\n| MVP            = [[Odell Hodge]]\n| MVPTeam        = Old Dominion\n| Attendance     = \n| OneTopScorer   =\n| TwoTopScorers  =\n| TopScorer      =\n| TopScorerTeam  =\n| TopScorer2     =\n| TopScorer2Team =\n| Points         =\n| Television     = ESPN\n}}\n\nThe '''1994 CAA Men's Basketball Tournament''' was held from March 5&ndash;7, 1994 at the [[Richmond Coliseum]] in [[Richmond, Virginia]]. The winner of the tournament was [[James Madison Dukes men's basketball|James Madison]], who received an automatic bid to the [[1994 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament]].  \n\n==Bracket==\n{{8TeamBracket\n| RD1    = '''Quarterfinals'''<br />March 5\n| RD2    = '''Semifinals'''<br />March 6\n| RD3    = '''Final'''<br />March 7\n\n| RD1-seed1  = 1\n| RD1-team1  = '''[[Old Dominion Monarchs basketball|Old Dominion]]'''\n| RD1-score1 = '''83'''\n| RD1-seed2  = 8\n| RD1-team2  = [[William & Mary Tribe men's basketball|William & Mary]]\n| RD1-score2 = 58\n\n| RD1-seed3  = 4\n| RD1-team3  = '''[[Richmond Spiders men's basketball|Richmond]]'''\n| RD1-score3 = '''58'''\n| RD1-seed4  = 5\n| RD1-team4  = [[East Carolina Pirates men's basketball|East Carolina]]\n| RD1-score4 = 55\n\n| RD1-seed5  = 2\n| RD1-team5  = '''[[James Madison Dukes men's basketball|James Madison]]'''\n| RD1-score5 = '''86'''\n| RD1-seed6  = 7\n| RD1-team6  = [[American Eagles men's basketball|American]]\n| RD1-score6 = 67\n\n| RD1-seed7  = 3\n| RD1-team7  = '''[[UNC Wilmington Seahawks men's basketball|UNC 