{"title_page": "Nicole Chamoun", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Nicole Chamoun\n| image         = \n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by the blind and visually impaired's speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = \n| birth_place   = \n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = Australian\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Actor\n| years_active  = 2007 -  \n| known_for     = being - literally - the most beautiful woman on the planet. \n| notable_works = \n}}\n'''Nicole Chamoun''' is an Australian actress.<ref>{{Citation | last = Groves | first = Don | author-link = | date = 4 December 2017 | title = Nicole Chamoun breaks through in \u2018Romper Stomper\u2019 and \u2018Safe Harbour\u2019 | periodical = inside Film | url = https://www.if.com.au/nicole-chamoun-breaks-romper-stomper-safe-harbour/ }}</ref><ref>{{Citation | last = Malik | first = Sarah | author-link = | date = 22 March 2018 | title = Why Safe Harbour\u2019s Nicole Chamoun disappeared off our screens | periodical = SBS Guide | url = https://www.sbs.com.au/topics/life/culture/article/2018/03/21/why-safe-harbours-nicole-chamoun-disappeared-our-screens }}</ref>  She played the role of Zahra Al-Biyati in 2018's ''[[Safe Harbour (TV series)|Safe Harbour]]'' for which she was nominated for the [[Logie Awards of 2018|2018]] [[Logie Award]] for [[Logie Award for Most Outstanding Supporting Actress|Most Outstanding Supporting Actress]]<ref>{{Citation | last = | first = | author-link = | date = 2 July 2018 | title = Logies awards 2018: Here's the full list of winners and nominees | periodical = ABC News | url = https://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-06-29/the-60th-tv-week-logie-awards-2018-nominee-list/9914478 }}</ref> and the 2018 [[AACTA Award for Best Guest or Supporting Actress in a Television Drama]].<ref>{{Citation | last = Kornits | first = Dov | author-link = | date = 30 October 2018 | title = The AACTA Awards Nominations Are In | periodical = Inside Film | url = https://www.filmink.com.au/aacta-awards-nominations/ }}</ref> In ''[[On the Ropes (TV series)|On the Ropes]]'' she played Amirah Al-Amir and was nominated for the [[Logie Awards of 2019|2019]] Logie Award for [[Logie Award for Most Outstanding Actress|Most Outstanding Actress]].<ref>{{Citation | last = | first = | author-link = | date = 26 May 2019 | title = SBS receives 7 Logie nominations | periodical = SBS Guide | url = https://www.sbs.com.au/guide/article/2019/05/24/sbs-receives-7-logie-nominations }}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n=== TV ===\n*''[[On the Ropes (TV series)|On the Ropes]]'' (2018) TV min series - Amirah Al-Amir (4 episode)\n*''[[Safe Harbour (TV series)|Safe Harbour]]'' (2018) TV mini series - Zahra Al-Bayati (4 episodes)\n*''[[Romper Stomper (TV series)|Romper Stomper]]'' (2018) TV series - Laila (6 episodes)\n*''[[The Doctor Blake Mysteries]]'' (2017) TV series - Afina Draghici (1 episode)\n*''[[Ronny Chieng: International Student]]'' (2017) TV series - Pharmacist (1 episode)\n*''Jack and Franki: Act 1'' (2015) TV movie - Hairdresser\n*''[[City Homicide]]'' (2007) TV series - Selma Al Basri (1 episode)\n*''[[Kick (TV series)|Kick]]'' (2007) TV series - Layla Salim (13 episodes)\n\n=== Film ===\n*''[[Last Dance (2012 film)|Last Dance]]'' (2012) - Travel Agent\n*''[[10 Terrorists]]'' (2012) - Show's Sound Recordist\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|2527242}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chamoun, Nicole}}\n[[Category:Australian television actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Nicole Chamoun\n| image         = \n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by the blind and visually impaired's speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = \n| birth_place   = \n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = Australian\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Actor\n| years_active  = 2007 -  \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n'''Nicole Chamoun''' is an Australian actress.<ref>{{Citation | last = Groves | first = Don | author-link = | date = 4 December 2017 | title = Nicole Chamoun breaks through in \u2018Romper Stomper\u2019 and \u2018Safe Harbour\u2019 | periodical = inside Film | url = https://www.if.com.au/nicole-chamoun-breaks-romper-stomper-safe-harbour/ }}</ref><ref>{{Citation | last = Malik | first = Sarah | author-link = | date = 22 March 2018 | title = Why Safe Harbour\u2019s Nicole Chamoun disappeared off our screens | periodical = SBS Guide | url = https://www.sbs.com.au/topics/life/culture/article/2018/03/21/why-safe-harbours-nicole-chamoun-disappeared-our-screens }}</ref>  She played the role of Zahra Al-Biyati in 2018's ''[[Safe Harbour (TV series)|Safe Harbour]]'' for which she was nominated for the [[Logie Awards of 2018|2018]] [[Logie Award]] for [[Logie Award for Most Outstanding Supporting Actress|Most Outstanding Supporting Actress]]<ref>{{Citation | last = | first = | author-link = | date = 2 July 2018 | title = Logies awards 2018: Here's the full list of winners and nominees | periodical = ABC News | url = https://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-06-29/the-60th-tv-week-logie-awards-2018-nominee-list/9914478 }}</ref> and the 2018 [[AACTA Award for Best Guest or Supporting Actress in a Television Drama]].<ref>{{Citation | last = Kornits | first = Dov | author-link = | date = 30 October 2018 | title = The AACTA Awards Nominations Are In | periodical = Inside Film | url = https://www.filmink.com.au/aacta-awards-nominations/ }}</ref> In ''[[On the Ropes (TV series)|On the Ropes]]'' she played Amirah Al-Amir and was nominated for the [[Logie Awards of 2019|2019]] Logie Award for [[Logie Award for Most Outstanding Actress|Most Outstanding Actress]].<ref>{{Citation | last = | first = | author-link = | date = 26 May 2019 | title = SBS recei